ecurity rivalry between the United States and China. Providing a much-needed account of state-technology affairs in the global south Cybersecurity Governance in Latin America challenges scholars and policymakers to rethink the protection of cyberspace to avoid unnecessarily sacrificing rights and freedoms in the name of national security.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aComputer securityxGovernment policyzLatin AmericavCase studies. 0aCyberspace operations (Military science) 0aCyberspace operations (Military science). 0aCyberspacexSecurity measureszLatin AmericavCase studies. 0aCyberterrorismxPreventionxGovernment policyzLatin America. 0aNational securityzLatin AmericavCase studies. 4aCriminology : Criminology. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Latin American Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Comparative Politics. 4aScience, Mathematics, and Technology : Internet. 4aSociology : Sociology of War. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849142440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438491424423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438491424/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles